# Trivy CVE exceptions for orkyo-community
#
# Format:
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN  # Impact | Reason | Added: YYYY-MM-DD | Review: YYYY-MM-DD
#
# Policy: time-bound only. Review date must be within 14 days of added date.
# Remove entries once the upstream fix is available.

# ── nginx:1.30-alpine — libexpat 2.8.2-r0 not yet in any published nginx image ──
# All nginx-alpine lines (1.30/1.31/mainline, Alpine 3.23) still ship libexpat
# 2.8.1-r0 (verified across tags 2026-07-09). nginx serves static assets only and
# parses no attacker-supplied XML via libexpat here.
CVE-2026-56131  # HIGH | libexpat <2.8.2 handler call depth (DoS) | upstream nginx-alpine not yet rebuilt with 2.8.2-r0 | Added: 2026-07-09 | Review: 2026-07-23
CVE-2026-56407  # HIGH | libexpat <2.8.2 integer overflow doProlog | upstream nginx-alpine not yet rebuilt with 2.8.2-r0 | Added: 2026-07-09 | Review: 2026-07-23
CVE-2026-56408  # HIGH | libexpat <2.8.2 integer overflow copyString | upstream nginx-alpine not yet rebuilt with 2.8.2-r0 | Added: 2026-07-09 | Review: 2026-07-23


# ── dotnet 10.0-alpine / node:22-alpine — openssl not yet rebuilt in base image ──
# openssl fix (3.5.7-r0) is in Alpine 3.23, but the pinned dotnet/aspnet,
# dotnet/runtime and node:22-alpine base images still ship 3.5.6-r0. apk upgrade
# is disallowed; nightly security-refresh.yml resolves once the bases are rebuilt.

# libcrypto3 / libssl3 3.5.6-r0 → 3.5.7-r0
CVE-2026-45447  # HIGH | openssl: heap use-after-free in PKCS7_verify() | Fix in Alpine 3.23 (3.5.7-r0); dotnet & node alpine bases not yet rebuilt | Added: 2026-06-14 | Review: 2026-06-21

# ── Trivy false positive ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Trivy reports fix as 12.6.5 but KC ships mssql-jdbc 13.2.1.jre11 (newer); false positive.
CVE-2025-59250  # HIGH | mssql-jdbc: improper input validation — Trivy lists fix as 12.6.5 but KC ships 13.2.1.jre11 (newer); false positive | Added: 2026-05-21 | Review: 2026-06-20
